# LangChain Documentation Index

When this repository involves **LangChain**, **LangGraph**, or **LangSmith** (anything under `src/`, or explicit user questions on those topics):

1. **Find the right page** using the official index: [https://docs.langchain.com/llms.txt](https://docs.langchain.com/llms.txt) — treat it as a sitemap of doc URLs, not full page content.
2. **Load details on demand** from the linked `.md` URLs (for example via the `docs-langchain` MCP server if configured, or a targeted fetch). Do not guess APIs or signatures from memory when the index or MCP can confirm them.
3. **Keep context lean** — do not paste the entire `llms.txt` into the chat; pick only the sections or URLs relevant to the task.

If the user asks about LangChain ecosystem topics outside `src/`, still follow steps 1–3 for that conversation.
